OL,3,CWhy has this motorway been named the
OL,4,Cworst in England?
OL,6,F"We're committed to working with the
OL,7,FGovernment and National Highways to
OL,8,Fhelp them to deliver on road users'
OL,9,Ftop priorities: improved journey times
OL,10,Fand satisfaction with surface quality."
OL,12,FGovernment-owned company National
OL,13,FHighways is responsible for England's
OL,14,Fmotorways and major A roads.
OL,16,FA National Highways spokesperson said
OL,17,F"Maintaining and investing in our
OL,18,Froads is a priority and our most
OL,19,Frecent assessment shows that over 96%
OL,20,Fof them are in good condition.
